3106int
3107rule_consistent(struct pf_rule *r, int anchor_call)
3108{
3109 int problems = 0;
3110
3111 switch (r->action) {
3112 case PF_PASS:
3113 case PF_DROP:
3114 case PF_SCRUB:
3115 case PF_NOSCRUB:
3116 problems = filter_consistent(r, anchor_call);
3117 break;
3118 case PF_NAT:
3119 case PF_NONAT:
3120 problems = nat_consistent(r);
3121 break;
3122 case PF_RDR:
3123 case PF_NORDR:
3124 problems = rdr_consistent(r);
3125 break;
3126 case PF_BINAT:
3127 case PF_NOBINAT:
3128 default:
3129 break;
3130 }
3131 return (problems);
3132}
3133
3134int
3135filter_consistent(struct pf_rule *r, int anchor_call)
3136{
3137 int problems = 0;
3138
3139 if (r->proto != IPPROTO_TCP && r->proto != IPPROTO_UDP &&
3140 (r->src.port_op || r->dst.port_op)) {
3141 yyerror("port only applies to tcp/udp");
3142 problems++;
3143 }
3144 if (r->proto != IPPROTO_ICMP && r->proto != IPPROTO_ICMPV6 &&
3145 (r->type || r->code)) {
3146 yyerror("icmp-type/code only applies to icmp");
3147 problems++;
3148 }
3149 if (!r->af && (r->type || r->code)) {
3150 yyerror("must indicate address family with icmp-type/code");
3151 problems++;
3152 }
3153 if (r->overload_tblname[0] &&
3154 r->max_src_conn == 0 && r->max_src_conn_rate.seconds == 0) {
3155 yyerror("'overload' requires 'max-src-conn' "
3156 "or 'max-src-conn-rate'");
3157 problems++;
3158 }
3159 if ((r->proto == IPPROTO_ICMP && r->af == AF_INET6) ||
3160 (r->proto == IPPROTO_ICMPV6 && r->af == AF_INET)) {
3161 yyerror("proto %s doesn't match address family %s",
3162 r->proto == IPPROTO_ICMP ? "icmp" : "icmp6",
3163 r->af == AF_INET ? "inet" : "inet6");
3164 problems++;
3165 }
3166 if (r->allow_opts && r->action != PF_PASS) {
3167 yyerror("allow-opts can only be specified for pass rules");
3168 problems++;
3169 }
3170 if (r->rule_flag & PFRULE_FRAGMENT && (r->src.port_op ||
3171 r->dst.port_op || r->flagset || r->type || r->code)) {
3172 yyerror("fragments can be filtered only on IP header fields");
3173 problems++;
3174 }
3175 if (r->rule_flag & PFRULE_RETURNRST && r->proto != IPPROTO_TCP) {
3176 yyerror("return-rst can only be applied to TCP rules");
3177 problems++;
3178 }
3179 if (r->max_src_nodes && !(r->rule_flag & PFRULE_RULESRCTRACK)) {
3180 yyerror("max-src-nodes requires 'source-track rule'");
3181 problems++;
3182 }
3183 if (r->action == PF_DROP && r->keep_state) {
3184 yyerror("keep state on block rules doesn't make sense");
3185 problems++;
3186 }
3187 return (-problems);
3188}

3191nat_consistent(struct pf_rule *r)
3192{
3193 return (0); /* yeah! */
3194}

3196int
3197rdr_consistent(struct pf_rule *r)
3198{
3199 int problems = 0;
3200
3201 if (r->proto != IPPROTO_TCP && r->proto != IPPROTO_UDP) {
3202 if (r->src.port_op) {
3203 yyerror("src port only applies to tcp/udp");
3204 problems++;
3205 }
3206 if (r->dst.port_op) {
3207 yyerror("dst port only applies to tcp/udp");
3208 problems++;
3209 }
3210 if (r->rpool.proxy_port[0]) {
3211 yyerror("rpool port only applies to tcp/udp");
3212 problems++;
3213 }
3214 }
3215 if (r->dst.port_op &&
3216 r->dst.port_op != PF_OP_EQ && r->dst.port_op != PF_OP_RRG) {
3217 yyerror("invalid port operator for rdr destination port");
3218 problems++;
3219 }
3220 return (-problems);
3221}

3223int
3224process_tabledef(char *name, struct table_opts *opts)
3225{
3226 struct pfr_buffer ab;
3227 struct node_tinit *ti;
3228
3229 bzero(&ab, sizeof(ab));
3230 ab.pfrb_type = PFRB_ADDRS;
3231 SIMPLEQ_FOREACH(ti, &opts->init_nodes, entries) {
3232 if (ti->file)
3233 if (pfr_buf_load(&ab, ti->file, 0, append_addr)) {
3234 if (errno)
3235 yyerror("cannot load \"%s\": %s",
3236 ti->file, strerror(errno));
3237 else
3238 yyerror("file \"%s\" contains bad data",
3239 ti->file);
3240 goto _error;
3241 }
3242 if (ti->host)
3243 if (append_addr_host(&ab, ti->host, 0, 0)) {
3244 yyerror("cannot create address buffer: %s",
3245 strerror(errno));
3246 goto _error;
3247 }
3248 }
3249 if (pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE)
3250 print_tabledef(name, opts->flags, opts->init_addr,
3251 &opts->init_nodes);
3252 if (!(pf->opts & PF_OPT_NOACTION) &&
3253 pfctl_define_table(name, opts->flags, opts->init_addr,
3254 pf->anchor->name, &ab, pf->anchor->ruleset.tticket)) {
3255 yyerror("cannot define table %s: %s", name,
3256 pfr_strerror(errno));
3257 goto _error;
3258 }
3259 pf->tdirty = 1;
3260 pfr_buf_clear(&ab);
3261 return (0);
3262_error:
3263 pfr_buf_clear(&ab);
3264 return (-1);

3302void
3303expand_label_str(char *label, size_t len, const char *srch, const char *repl)
3304{
3305 char *tmp;
3306 char *p, *q;
3307
3308 if ((tmp = calloc(1, len)) == NULL)
3309 err(1, "expand_label_str: calloc");
3310 p = q = label;
3311 while ((q = strstr(p, srch)) != NULL) {
3312 *q = '\0';
3313 if ((strlcat(tmp, p, len) >= len) ||
3314 (strlcat(tmp, repl, len) >= len))
3315 errx(1, "expand_label: label too long");
3316 q += strlen(srch);
3317 p = q;
3318 }
3319 if (strlcat(tmp, p, len) >= len)
3320 errx(1, "expand_label: label too long");
3321 strlcpy(label, tmp, len); /* always fits */
3322 free(tmp);
3323}

3336void
3337expand_label_addr(const char *name, char *label, size_t len, sa_family_t af,
3338 struct node_host *h)
3339{
3340 char tmp[64], tmp_not[66];
3341
3342 if (strstr(label, name) != NULL) {
3343 switch (h->addr.type) {
3344 case PF_ADDR_DYNIFTL:
3345 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "(%s)", h->addr.v.ifname);
3346 break;
3347 case PF_ADDR_TABLE:
3348 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "<%s>", h->addr.v.tblname);
3349 break;
3350 case PF_ADDR_NOROUTE:
3351 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "no-route");
3352 break;
3353 case PF_ADDR_URPFFAILED:
3354 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "urpf-failed");
3355 break;
3356 case PF_ADDR_ADDRMASK:
3357 if (!af || (PF_AZERO(&h->addr.v.a.addr, af) &&
3358 PF_AZERO(&h->addr.v.a.mask, af)))
3359 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "any");
3360 else {
3361 char a[48];
3362 int bits;
3363
3364 if (inet_ntop(af, &h->addr.v.a.addr, a,
3365 sizeof(a)) == NULL)
3366 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "?");
3367 else {
3368 bits = unmask(&h->addr.v.a.mask, af);
3369 if ((af == AF_INET && bits < 32) ||
3370 (af == AF_INET6 && bits < 128))
3371 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp),
3372 "%s/%d", a, bits);
3373 else
3374 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp),
3375 "%s", a);
3376 }
3377 }
3378 break;
3379 default:
3380 snprintf(tmp, sizeof(tmp), "?");
3381 break;
3382 }
3383
3384 if (h->not) {
3385 snprintf(tmp_not, sizeof(tmp_not), "! %s", tmp);
3386 expand_label_str(label, len, name, tmp_not);
3387 } else
3388 expand_label_str(label, len, name, tmp);
3389 }
3390}

3392void
3393expand_label_port(const char *name, char *label, size_t len,
3394 struct node_port *port)
3395{
3396 char a1[6], a2[6], op[13] = "";
3397
3398 if (strstr(label, name) != NULL) {
3399 snprintf(a1, sizeof(a1), "%u", ntohs(port->port[0]));
3400 snprintf(a2, sizeof(a2), "%u", ntohs(port->port[1]));
3401 if (!port->op)
3402 ;
3403 else if (port->op == PF_OP_IRG)
3404 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), "%s><%s", a1, a2);
3405 else if (port->op == PF_OP_XRG)
3406 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), "%s<>%s", a1, a2);
3407 else if (port->op == PF_OP_EQ)
3408 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), "%s", a1);
3409 else if (port->op == PF_OP_NE)
3410 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), "!=%s", a1);
3411 else if (port->op == PF_OP_LT)
3412 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), "<%s", a1);
3413 else if (port->op == PF_OP_LE)
3414 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), "<=%s", a1);
3415 else if (port->op == PF_OP_GT)
3416 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), ">%s", a1);
3417 else if (port->op == PF_OP_GE)
3418 snprintf(op, sizeof(op), ">=%s", a1);
3419 expand_label_str(label, len, name, op);
3420 }

3522 sizeof(qname)) >= sizeof(qname))
3523 errx(1, "expand_altq: strlcat");
3524 if (strlcpy(pb.qname, qname,
3525 sizeof(pb.qname)) >= sizeof(pb.qname))
3526 errx(1, "expand_altq: strlcpy");
3527 if (strlcpy(pb.ifname, interface->ifname,
3528 sizeof(pb.ifname)) >= sizeof(pb.ifname))
3529 errx(1, "expand_altq: strlcpy");
3530 pb.qlimit = pa.qlimit;
3531 pb.scheduler = pa.scheduler;
3532 bw.bw_absolute = pa.ifbandwidth;
3533 bw.bw_percent = 0;
3534 if (eval_pfqueue(pf, &pb, &bw, opts))
3535 errs++;
3536 else
3537 if (pfctl_add_altq(pf, &pb))
3538 errs++;
3539 }
3540
3541 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_queue, queue, nqueues,
3542 n = calloc(1, sizeof(struct node_queue));
3543 if (n == NULL)
3544 err(1, "expand_altq: calloc");
3545 if (pa.scheduler == ALTQT_CBQ ||
3546 pa.scheduler == ALTQT_HFSC)
3547 if (strlcpy(n->parent, qname,
3548 sizeof(n->parent)) >=
3549 sizeof(n->parent))
3550 errx(1, "expand_altq: strlcpy");
3551 if (strlcpy(n->queue, queue->queue,
3552 sizeof(n->queue)) >= sizeof(n->queue))
3553 errx(1, "expand_altq: strlcpy");
3554 if (strlcpy(n->ifname, interface->ifname,
3555 sizeof(n->ifname)) >= sizeof(n->ifname))
3556 errx(1, "expand_altq: strlcpy");
3557 n->scheduler = pa.scheduler;
3558 n->next = NULL;
3559 n->tail = n;
3560 if (queues == NULL)
3561 queues = n;
3562 else {
3563 queues->tail->next = n;
3564 queues->tail = n;
3565 }
3566 );
3567 }
3568 );
3569 FREE_LIST(struct node_if, interfaces);
3570 FREE_LIST(struct node_queue, nqueues);
3571
3572 return (errs);
3573}
3574
3575int
3576expand_queue(struct pf_altq *a, struct node_if *interfaces,
3577 struct node_queue *nqueues, struct node_queue_bw bwspec,
3578 struct node_queue_opt *opts)
3579{
3580 struct node_queue *n, *nq;
3581 struct pf_altq pa;
3582 u_int8_t found = 0;
3583 u_int8_t errs = 0;
3584
3585 if ((pf->loadopt & PFCTL_FLAG_ALTQ) == 0) {
3586 FREE_LIST(struct node_queue, nqueues);
3587 return (0);
3588 }
3589
3590 if (queues == NULL) {
3591 yyerror("queue %s has no parent", a->qname);
3592 FREE_LIST(struct node_queue, nqueues);
3593 return (1);
3594 }
3595
3596 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_if, interface, interfaces,
3597 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_queue, tqueue, queues,
3598 if (!strncmp(a->qname, tqueue->queue, PF_QNAME_SIZE) &&
3599 (interface->ifname[0] == 0 ||
3600 (!interface->not && !strncmp(interface->ifname,
3601 tqueue->ifname, IFNAMSIZ)) ||
3602 (interface->not && strncmp(interface->ifname,
3603 tqueue->ifname, IFNAMSIZ)))) {
3604 /* found ourself in queues */
3605 found++;
3606
3607 memcpy(&pa, a, sizeof(struct pf_altq));
3608
3609 if (pa.scheduler != ALTQT_NONE &&
3610 pa.scheduler != tqueue->scheduler) {
3611 yyerror("exactly one scheduler type "
3612 "per interface allowed");
3613 errs++;
3614 goto out;
3615 }
3616 pa.scheduler = tqueue->scheduler;
3617
3618 /* scheduler dependent error checking */
3619 switch (pa.scheduler) {
3620 case ALTQT_PRIQ:
3621 if (nqueues != NULL) {
3622 yyerror("priq queues cannot "
3623 "have child queues");
3624 errs++;
3625 goto out;
3626 }
3627 if (bwspec.bw_absolute > 0 ||
3628 bwspec.bw_percent < 100) {
3629 yyerror("priq doesn't take "
3630 "bandwidth");
3631 errs++;
3632 goto out;
3633 }
3634 break;
3635 default:
3636 break;
3637 }
3638
3639 if (strlcpy(pa.ifname, tqueue->ifname,
3640 sizeof(pa.ifname)) >= sizeof(pa.ifname))
3641 errx(1, "expand_queue: strlcpy");
3642 if (strlcpy(pa.parent, tqueue->parent,
3643 sizeof(pa.parent)) >= sizeof(pa.parent))
3644 errx(1, "expand_queue: strlcpy");
3645
3646 if (eval_pfqueue(pf, &pa, &bwspec, opts))
3647 errs++;
3648 else
3649 if (pfctl_add_altq(pf, &pa))
3650 errs++;
3651
3652 for (nq = nqueues; nq != NULL; nq = nq->next) {
3653 if (!strcmp(a->qname, nq->queue)) {
3654 yyerror("queue cannot have "
3655 "itself as child");
3656 errs++;
3657 continue;
3658 }
3659 n = calloc(1,
3660 sizeof(struct node_queue));
3661 if (n == NULL)
3662 err(1, "expand_queue: calloc");
3663 if (strlcpy(n->parent, a->qname,
3664 sizeof(n->parent)) >=
3665 sizeof(n->parent))
3666 errx(1, "expand_queue strlcpy");
3667 if (strlcpy(n->queue, nq->queue,
3668 sizeof(n->queue)) >=
3669 sizeof(n->queue))
3670 errx(1, "expand_queue strlcpy");
3671 if (strlcpy(n->ifname, tqueue->ifname,
3672 sizeof(n->ifname)) >=
3673 sizeof(n->ifname))
3674 errx(1, "expand_queue strlcpy");
3675 n->scheduler = tqueue->scheduler;
3676 n->next = NULL;
3677 n->tail = n;
3678 if (queues == NULL)
3679 queues = n;
3680 else {
3681 queues->tail->next = n;
3682 queues->tail = n;
3683 }
3684 }
3685 if ((pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE) && (
3686 (found == 1 && interface->ifname[0] == 0) ||
3687 (found > 0 && interface->ifname[0] != 0))) {
3688 print_queue(&pf->paltq->altq, 0,
3689 &bwspec, interface->ifname[0] != 0,
3690 opts);
3691 if (nqueues && nqueues->tail) {
3692 printf("{ ");
3693 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_queue,
3694 queue, nqueues,
3695 printf("%s ",
3696 queue->queue);
3697 );
3698 printf("}");
3699 }
3700 printf("\n");
3701 }
3702 }
3703 );
3704 );
3705
3706out:
3707 FREE_LIST(struct node_queue, nqueues);
3708 FREE_LIST(struct node_if, interfaces);
3709
3710 if (!found) {
3711 yyerror("queue %s has no parent", a->qname);
3712 errs++;
3713 }
3714
3715 if (errs)
3716 return (1);
3717 else
3718 return (0);
3719}
3720
3721void
3722expand_rule(struct pf_rule *r,
3723 struct node_if *interfaces, struct node_host *rpool_hosts,
3724 struct node_proto *protos, struct node_os *src_oses,
3725 struct node_host *src_hosts, struct node_port *src_ports,
3726 struct node_host *dst_hosts, struct node_port *dst_ports,
3727 struct node_uid *uids, struct node_gid *gids, struct node_icmp *icmp_types,
3728 const char *anchor_call)
3729{
3730 sa_family_t af = r->af;
3731 int added = 0, error = 0;
3732 char ifname[IF_NAMESIZE];
3733 char label[PF_RULE_LABEL_SIZE];
3734 char tagname[PF_TAG_NAME_SIZE];
3735 char match_tagname[PF_TAG_NAME_SIZE];
3736 struct pf_pooladdr *pa;
3737 struct node_host *h;
3738 u_int8_t flags, flagset, keep_state;
3739
3740 if (strlcpy(label, r->label, sizeof(label)) >= sizeof(label))
3741 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3742 if (strlcpy(tagname, r->tagname, sizeof(tagname)) >= sizeof(tagname))
3743 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3744 if (strlcpy(match_tagname, r->match_tagname, sizeof(match_tagname)) >=
3745 sizeof(match_tagname))
3746 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3747 flags = r->flags;
3748 flagset = r->flagset;
3749 keep_state = r->keep_state;
3750
3751 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_if, interface, interfaces,
3752 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_proto, proto, protos,
3753 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_icmp, icmp_type, icmp_types,
3754 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_host, src_host, src_hosts,
3755 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_port, src_port, src_ports,
3756 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_os, src_os, src_oses,
3757 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_host, dst_host, dst_hosts,
3758 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_port, dst_port, dst_ports,
3759 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_uid, uid, uids,
3760 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_gid, gid, gids,
3761
3762 r->af = af;
3763 /* for link-local IPv6 address, interface must match up */
3764 if ((r->af && src_host->af && r->af != src_host->af) ||
3765 (r->af && dst_host->af && r->af != dst_host->af) ||
3766 (src_host->af && dst_host->af &&
3767 src_host->af != dst_host->af) ||
3768 (src_host->ifindex && dst_host->ifindex &&
3769 src_host->ifindex != dst_host->ifindex) ||
3770 (src_host->ifindex && *interface->ifname &&
3771 src_host->ifindex != if_nametoindex(interface->ifname)) ||
3772 (dst_host->ifindex && *interface->ifname &&
3773 dst_host->ifindex != if_nametoindex(interface->ifname)))
3774 continue;
3775 if (!r->af && src_host->af)
3776 r->af = src_host->af;
3777 else if (!r->af && dst_host->af)
3778 r->af = dst_host->af;
3779
3780 if (*interface->ifname)
3781 strlcpy(r->ifname, interface->ifname,
3782 sizeof(r->ifname));
3783 else if (if_indextoname(src_host->ifindex, ifname))
3784 strlcpy(r->ifname, ifname, sizeof(r->ifname));
3785 else if (if_indextoname(dst_host->ifindex, ifname))
3786 strlcpy(r->ifname, ifname, sizeof(r->ifname));
3787 else
3788 memset(r->ifname, '\0', sizeof(r->ifname));
3789
3790 if (strlcpy(r->label, label, sizeof(r->label)) >=
3791 sizeof(r->label))
3792 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3793 if (strlcpy(r->tagname, tagname, sizeof(r->tagname)) >=
3794 sizeof(r->tagname))
3795 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3796 if (strlcpy(r->match_tagname, match_tagname,
3797 sizeof(r->match_tagname)) >= sizeof(r->match_tagname))
3798 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3799 expand_label(r->label, PF_RULE_LABEL_SIZE, r->ifname, r->af,
3800 src_host, src_port, dst_host, dst_port, proto->proto);
3801 expand_label(r->tagname, PF_TAG_NAME_SIZE, r->ifname, r->af,
3802 src_host, src_port, dst_host, dst_port, proto->proto);
3803 expand_label(r->match_tagname, PF_TAG_NAME_SIZE, r->ifname,
3804 r->af, src_host, src_port, dst_host, dst_port,
3805 proto->proto);
3806
3807 error += check_netmask(src_host, r->af);
3808 error += check_netmask(dst_host, r->af);
3809
3810 r->ifnot = interface->not;
3811 r->proto = proto->proto;
3812 r->src.addr = src_host->addr;
3813 r->src.neg = src_host->not;
3814 r->src.port[0] = src_port->port[0];
3815 r->src.port[1] = src_port->port[1];
3816 r->src.port_op = src_port->op;
3817 r->dst.addr = dst_host->addr;
3818 r->dst.neg = dst_host->not;
3819 r->dst.port[0] = dst_port->port[0];
3820 r->dst.port[1] = dst_port->port[1];
3821 r->dst.port_op = dst_port->op;
3822 r->uid.op = uid->op;
3823 r->uid.uid[0] = uid->uid[0];
3824 r->uid.uid[1] = uid->uid[1];
3825 r->gid.op = gid->op;
3826 r->gid.gid[0] = gid->gid[0];
3827 r->gid.gid[1] = gid->gid[1];
3828 r->type = icmp_type->type;
3829 r->code = icmp_type->code;
3830
3831 if ((keep_state == PF_STATE_MODULATE ||
3832 keep_state == PF_STATE_SYNPROXY) &&
3833 r->proto && r->proto != IPPROTO_TCP)
3834 r->keep_state = PF_STATE_NORMAL;
3835 else
3836 r->keep_state = keep_state;
3837
3838 if (r->proto && r->proto != IPPROTO_TCP) {
3839 r->flags = 0;
3840 r->flagset = 0;
3841 } else {
3842 r->flags = flags;
3843 r->flagset = flagset;
3844 }
3845 if (icmp_type->proto && r->proto != icmp_type->proto) {
3846 yyerror("icmp-type mismatch");
3847 error++;
3848 }
3849
3850 if (src_os && src_os->os) {
3851 r->os_fingerprint = pfctl_get_fingerprint(src_os->os);
3852 if ((pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE2) &&
3853 r->os_fingerprint == PF_OSFP_NOMATCH)
3854 fprintf(stderr,
3855 "warning: unknown '%s' OS fingerprint\n",
3856 src_os->os);
3857 } else {
3858 r->os_fingerprint = PF_OSFP_ANY;
3859 }
3860
3861 TAILQ_INIT(&r->rpool.list);
3862 for (h = rpool_hosts; h != NULL; h = h->next) {
3863 pa = calloc(1, sizeof(struct pf_pooladdr));
3864 if (pa == NULL)
3865 err(1, "expand_rule: calloc");
3866 pa->addr = h->addr;
3867 if (h->ifname != NULL) {
3868 if (strlcpy(pa->ifname, h->ifname,
3869 sizeof(pa->ifname)) >=
3870 sizeof(pa->ifname))
3871 errx(1, "expand_rule: strlcpy");
3872 } else
3873 pa->ifname[0] = 0;
3874 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&r->rpool.list, pa, entries);
3875 }
3876
3877 if (rule_consistent(r, anchor_call[0]) < 0 || error)
3878 yyerror("skipping rule due to errors");
3879 else {
3880 r->nr = pf->astack[pf->asd]->match++;
3881 pfctl_add_rule(pf, r, anchor_call);
3882 added++;
3883 }
3884
3885 ))))))))));
3886
3887 FREE_LIST(struct node_if, interfaces);
3888 FREE_LIST(struct node_proto, protos);
3889 FREE_LIST(struct node_host, src_hosts);
3890 FREE_LIST(struct node_port, src_ports);
3891 FREE_LIST(struct node_os, src_oses);
3892 FREE_LIST(struct node_host, dst_hosts);
3893 FREE_LIST(struct node_port, dst_ports);
3894 FREE_LIST(struct node_uid, uids);
3895 FREE_LIST(struct node_gid, gids);
3896 FREE_LIST(struct node_icmp, icmp_types);
3897 FREE_LIST(struct node_host, rpool_hosts);
3898
3899 if (!added)
3900 yyerror("rule expands to no valid combination");
3901}

3903int
3904expand_skip_interface(struct node_if *interfaces)
3905{
3906 int errs = 0;
3907
3908 if (!interfaces || (!interfaces->next && !interfaces->not &&
3909 !strcmp(interfaces->ifname, "none"))) {
3910 if (pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE)
3911 printf("set skip on none\n");
3912 errs = pfctl_set_interface_flags(pf, "", PFI_IFLAG_SKIP, 0);
3913 return (errs);
3914 }
3915
3916 if (pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE)
3917 printf("set skip on {");
3918 LOOP_THROUGH(struct node_if, interface, interfaces,
3919 if (pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE)
3920 printf(" %s", interface->ifname);
3921 if (interface->not) {
3922 yyerror("skip on ! <interface> is not supported");
3923 errs++;
3924 } else
3925 errs += pfctl_set_interface_flags(pf,
3926 interface->ifname, PFI_IFLAG_SKIP, 1);
3927 );
3928 if (pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE)
3929 printf(" }\n");
3930
3931 FREE_LIST(struct node_if, interfaces);
3932
3933 if (errs)
3934 return (1);
3935 else
3936 return (0);
3937}

3942int
3943check_rulestate(int desired_state)
3944{
3945 if (require_order && (rulestate > desired_state)) {
3946 yyerror("Rules must be in order: options, normalization, "
3947 "queueing, translation, filtering");
3948 return (1);
3949 }
3950 rulestate = desired_state;
3951 return (0);
3952}

4093
4094#define MAXPUSHBACK 128
4095
4096char *parsebuf;
4097int parseindex;
4098char pushback_buffer[MAXPUSHBACK];
4099int pushback_index = 0;
4100
4101int
4102lgetc(FILE *f)
4103{
4104 int c, next;
4105
4106 if (parsebuf) {
4107 /* Read character from the parsebuffer instead of input. */
4108 if (parseindex >= 0) {
4109 c = parsebuf[parseindex++];
4110 if (c != '\0')
4111 return (c);
4112 parsebuf = NULL;
4113 } else
4114 parseindex++;
4115 }
4116
4117 if (pushback_index)
4118 return (pushback_buffer[--pushback_index]);
4119
4120 while ((c = getc(f)) == '\\') {
4121 next = getc(f);
4122 if (next != '\n') {
4123 c = next;
4124 break;
4125 }
4126 yylval.lineno = lineno;
4127 lineno++;
4128 }
4129 if (c == '\t' || c == ' ') {
4130 /* Compress blanks to a single space. */
4131 do {
4132 c = getc(f);
4133 } while (c == '\t' || c == ' ');
4134 ungetc(c, f);
4135 c = ' ';
4136 }
4137
4138 return (c);
4139}
4140
4141int
4142lungetc(int c)
4143{
4144 if (c == EOF)
4145 return (EOF);
4146 if (parsebuf) {
4147 parseindex--;
4148 if (parseindex >= 0)
4149 return (c);
4150 }
4151 if (pushback_index < MAXPUSHBACK-1)
4152 return (pushback_buffer[pushback_index++] = c);
4153 else
4154 return (EOF);
4155}
4156
4157int
4158findeol(void)
4159{
4160 int c;
4161
4162 parsebuf = NULL;
4163 pushback_index = 0;
4164
4165 /* skip to either EOF or the first real EOL */
4166 while (1) {
4167 c = lgetc(fin);
4168 if (c == '\n') {
4169 lineno++;
4170 break;
4171 }
4172 if (c == EOF)
4173 break;
4174 }
4175 return (ERROR);
4176}
4177
4178int
4179yylex(void)
4180{
4181 char buf[8096];
4182 char *p, *val;
4183 int endc, c, next;
4184 int token;
4185
4186top:
4187 p = buf;
4188 while ((c = lgetc(fin)) == ' ')
4189 ; /* nothing */
4190
4191 yylval.lineno = lineno;
4192 if (c == '#')
4193 while ((c = lgetc(fin)) != '\n' && c != EOF)
4194 ; /* nothing */
4195 if (c == '$' && parsebuf == NULL) {
4196 while (1) {
4197 if ((c = lgetc(fin)) == EOF)
4198 return (0);
4199
4200 if (p + 1 >= buf + sizeof(buf) - 1) {
4201 yyerror("string too long");
4202 return (findeol());
4203 }
4204 if (isalnum(c) || c == '_') {
4205 *p++ = (char)c;
4206 continue;
4207 }
4208 *p = '\0';
4209 lungetc(c);
4210 break;
4211 }
4212 val = symget(buf);
4213 if (val == NULL) {
4214 yyerror("macro '%s' not defined", buf);
4215 return (findeol());
4216 }
4217 parsebuf = val;
4218 parseindex = 0;
4219 goto top;
4220 }
4221
4222 switch (c) {
4223 case '\'':
4224 case '"':
4225 endc = c;
4226 while (1) {
4227 if ((c = lgetc(fin)) == EOF)
4228 return (0);
4229 if (c == endc) {
4230 *p = '\0';
4231 break;
4232 }
4233 if (c == '\n') {
4234 lineno++;
4235 continue;
4236 }
4237 if (p + 1 >= buf + sizeof(buf) - 1) {
4238 yyerror("string too long");
4239 return (findeol());
4240 }
4241 *p++ = (char)c;
4242 }
4243 yylval.v.string = strdup(buf);
4244 if (yylval.v.string == NULL)
4245 err(1, "yylex: strdup");
4246 return (STRING);
4247 case '<':
4248 next = lgetc(fin);
4249 if (next == '>') {
4250 yylval.v.i = PF_OP_XRG;
4251 return (PORTBINARY);
4252 }
4253 lungetc(next);
4254 break;
4255 case '>':
4256 next = lgetc(fin);
4257 if (next == '<') {
4258 yylval.v.i = PF_OP_IRG;
4259 return (PORTBINARY);
4260 }
4261 lungetc(next);
4262 break;
4263 case '-':
4264 next = lgetc(fin);
4265 if (next == '>')
4266 return (ARROW);
4267 lungetc(next);
4268 break;
4269 }
4270
4271#define allowed_in_string(x) \
4272 (isalnum(x) || (ispunct(x) && x != '(' && x != ')' && \
4273 x != '{' && x != '}' && x != '<' && x != '>' && \
4274 x != '!' && x != '=' && x != '/' && x != '#' && \
4275 x != ','))
4276
4277 if (isalnum(c) || c == ':' || c == '_') {
4278 do {
4279 *p++ = c;
4280 if ((unsigned)(p-buf) >= sizeof(buf)) {
4281 yyerror("string too long");
4282 return (findeol());
4283 }
4284 } while ((c = lgetc(fin)) != EOF && (allowed_in_string(c)));
4285 lungetc(c);
4286 *p = '\0';
4287 if ((token = lookup(buf)) == STRING)
4288 if ((yylval.v.string = strdup(buf)) == NULL)
4289 err(1, "yylex: strdup");
4290 return (token);
4291 }
4292 if (c == '\n') {
4293 yylval.lineno = lineno;
4294 lineno++;
4295 }
4296 if (c == EOF)
4297 return (0);
4298 return (c);
4299}

4301int
4302parse_rules(FILE *input, struct pfctl *xpf)
4303{
4304 struct sym *sym, *next;
4305
4306 fin = input;
4307 pf = xpf;
4308 lineno = 1;
4309 errors = 0;
4310 rulestate = PFCTL_STATE_NONE;
4311 returnicmpdefault = (ICMP_UNREACH << 8) | ICMP_UNREACH_PORT;
4312 returnicmp6default =
4313 (ICMP6_DST_UNREACH << 8) | ICMP6_DST_UNREACH_NOPORT;
4314 blockpolicy = PFRULE_DROP;
4315 require_order = 1;
4316
4317 yyparse();
4318
4319 /* Free macros and check which have not been used. */
4320 for (sym = TAILQ_FIRST(&symhead); sym != NULL; sym = next) {
4321 next = TAILQ_NEXT(sym, entries);
4322 if ((pf->opts & PF_OPT_VERBOSE2) && !sym->used)
4323 fprintf(stderr, "warning: macro '%s' not "
4324 "used\n", sym->nam);
4325 free(sym->nam);
4326 free(sym->val);
4327 TAILQ_REMOVE(&symhead, sym, entries);
4328 free(sym);
4329 }
4330
4331 return (errors ? -1 : 0);
4332}

4334/*
4335 * Over-designed efficiency is a French and German concept, so how about
4336 * we wait until they discover this ugliness and make it all fancy.
4337 */
4338int
4339symset(const char *nam, const char *val, int persist)
4340{
4341 struct sym *sym;
4342
4343 for (sym = TAILQ_FIRST(&symhead); sym && strcmp(nam, sym->nam);
4344 sym = TAILQ_NEXT(sym, entries))
4345 ; /* nothing */
4346
4347 if (sym != NULL) {
4348 if (sym->persist == 1)
4349 return (0);
4350 else {
4351 free(sym->nam);
4352 free(sym->val);
4353 TAILQ_REMOVE(&symhead, sym, entries);
4354 free(sym);
4355 }
4356 }
4357 if ((sym = calloc(1, sizeof(*sym))) == NULL)
4358 return (-1);
4359
4360 sym->nam = strdup(nam);
4361 if (sym->nam == NULL) {
4362 free(sym);
4363 return (-1);
4364 }
4365 sym->val = strdup(val);
4366 if (sym->val == NULL) {
4367 free(sym->nam);
4368 free(sym);
4369 return (-1);
4370 }
4371 sym->used = 0;
4372 sym->persist = persist;
4373 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(&symhead, sym, entries);
4374 return (0);
4375}
4376
4377int
4378pfctl_cmdline_symset(char *s)
4379{
4380 char *sym, *val;
4381 int ret;
4382
4383 if ((val = strrchr(s, '=')) == NULL)
4384 return (-1);
4385
4386 if ((sym = malloc(strlen(s) - strlen(val) + 1)) == NULL)
4387 err(1, "pfctl_cmdline_symset: malloc");
4388
4389 strlcpy(sym, s, strlen(s) - strlen(val) + 1);
4390
4391 ret = symset(sym, val + 1, 1);
4392 free(sym);
4393
4394 return (ret);
4395}

4401

4410void
4411mv_rules(struct pf_ruleset *src, struct pf_ruleset *dst)
4412{
4413 int i;
4414 struct pf_rule *r;
4415
4416 for (i = 0; i < PF_RULESET_MAX; ++i) {
4417 while ((r = TAILQ_FIRST(src->rules[i].active.ptr))
4418 != NULL) {
4419 TAILQ_REMOVE(src->rules[i].active.ptr, r, entries);
4420 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(dst->rules[i].active.ptr, r, entries);
4421 dst->anchor->match++;
4422 }
4423 src->anchor->match = 0;
4424 while ((r = TAILQ_FIRST(src->rules[i].inactive.ptr))
4425 != NULL) {
4426 TAILQ_REMOVE(src->rules[i].inactive.ptr, r, entries);
4427 TAILQ_INSERT_TAIL(dst->rules[i].inactive.ptr,
4428 r, entries);
4429 }
4430 }

4433void
4434decide_address_family(struct node_host *n, sa_family_t *af)
4435{
4436 if (*af != 0 || n == NULL)
4437 return;
4438 *af = n->af;
4439 while ((n = n->next) != NULL) {
4440 if (n->af != *af) {
4441 *af = 0;
4442 return;
4443 }
4444 }
4445}

4447void
4448remove_invalid_hosts(struct node_host **nh, sa_family_t *af)
4449{
4450 struct node_host *n = *nh, *prev = NULL;
4451
4452 while (n != NULL) {
4453 if (*af && n->af && n->af != *af) {
4454 /* unlink and free n */
4455 struct node_host *next = n->next;
4456
4457 /* adjust tail pointer */
4458 if (n == (*nh)->tail)
4459 (*nh)->tail = prev;
4460 /* adjust previous node's next pointer */
4461 if (prev == NULL)
4462 *nh = next;
4463 else
4464 prev->next = next;
4465 /* free node */
4466 if (n->ifname != NULL)
4467 free(n->ifname);
4468 free(n);
4469 n = next;
4470 } else {
4471 if (n->af && !*af)
4472 *af = n->af;
4473 prev = n;
4474 n = n->next;
4475 }
4476 }
4477}

4479int
4480invalid_redirect(struct node_host *nh, sa_family_t af)
4481{
4482 if (!af) {
4483 struct node_host *n;
4484
4485 /* tables and dyniftl are ok without an address family */
4486 for (n = nh; n != NULL; n = n->next) {
4487 if (n->addr.type != PF_ADDR_TABLE &&
4488 n->addr.type != PF_ADDR_DYNIFTL) {
4489 yyerror("address family not given and "
4490 "translation address expands to multiple "
4491 "address families");
4492 return (1);
4493 }
4494 }
4495 }
4496 if (nh == NULL) {
4497 yyerror("no translation address with matching address family "
4498 "found.");
4499 return (1);
4500 }
4501 return (0);

4558u_int16_t
4559parseicmpspec(char *w, sa_family_t af)
4560{
4561 const struct icmpcodeent *p;
4562 u_long ulval;
4563 u_int8_t icmptype;
4564
4565 if (af == AF_INET)
4566 icmptype = returnicmpdefault >> 8;
4567 else
4568 icmptype = returnicmp6default >> 8;
4569
4570 if (atoul(w, &ulval) == -1) {
4571 if ((p = geticmpcodebyname(icmptype, w, af)) == NULL) {
4572 yyerror("unknown icmp code %s", w);
4573 return (0);
4574 }
4575 ulval = p->code;
4576 }
4577 if (ulval > 255) {
4578 yyerror("invalid icmp code %lu", ulval);
4579 return (0);
4580 }
4581 return (icmptype << 8 | ulval);
4582}

9504 yystate = yydgoto[yym];
9505#if YYDEBUG
9506 if (yydebug)
9507 {
9508 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: after reduction, ", YYDEBUGSTR, yydepth);
9509#ifdef YYSTYPE_TOSTRING
9510#if YYBTYACC
9511 if (!yytrial)
9512#endif /* YYBTYACC */
9513 fprintf(stderr, "result is <%s>, ", YYSTYPE_TOSTRING(yystos[yystate], yyval));
9514#endif
9515 fprintf(stderr, "shifting from state %d to state %d\n", *yystack.s_mark, yystate);
9516 }
9517#endif
9518 if (yystack.s_mark >= yystack.s_last && yygrowstack(&yystack) == YYENOMEM) goto yyoverflow;
9519 *++yystack.s_mark = (YYINT) yystate;
9520 *++yystack.l_mark = yyval;
9521#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
9522 *++yystack.p_mark = yyloc;
9523#endif
9524 goto yyloop;
9525#if YYBTYACC
9526
9527 /* Reduction declares that this path is valid. Set yypath and do a full parse */
9528yyvalid:
9529 if (yypath) YYABORT;
9530 while (yyps->save)
9531 {
9532 YYParseState *save = yyps->save;
9533 yyps->save = save->save;
9534 save->save = yypath;
9535 yypath = save;
9536 }
9537#if YYDEBUG
9538 if (yydebug)
9539 fprintf(stderr, "%s[%d]: state %d, CONFLICT trial successful, backtracking to state %d, %d tokens\n",
9540 YYDEBUGSTR, yydepth, yystate, yypath->state, (int)(yylvp - yylvals - yypath->lexeme));
9541#endif
9542 if (yyerrctx)
9543 {
9544 yyFreeState(yyerrctx);
9545 yyerrctx = NULL;
9546 }
9547 yylvp = yylvals + yypath->lexeme;
9548#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
9549 yylpp = yylpsns + yypath->lexeme;
9550#endif
9551 yylexp = yylexemes + yypath->lexeme;
9552 yychar = YYEMPTY;
9553 yystack.s_mark = yystack.s_base + (yypath->yystack.s_mark - yypath->yystack.s_base);
9554 memcpy (yystack.s_base, yypath->yystack.s_base, (size_t) (yystack.s_mark - yystack.s_base + 1) * sizeof(YYINT));
9555 yystack.l_mark = yystack.l_base + (yypath->yystack.l_mark - yypath->yystack.l_base);
9556 memcpy (yystack.l_base, yypath->yystack.l_base, (size_t) (yystack.l_mark - yystack.l_base + 1) * sizeof(YYSTYPE));
9557#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
9558 yystack.p_mark = yystack.p_base + (yypath->yystack.p_mark - yypath->yystack.p_base);
9559 memcpy (yystack.p_base, yypath->yystack.p_base, (size_t) (yystack.p_mark - yystack.p_base + 1) * sizeof(YYLTYPE));
9560#endif
9561 yystate = yypath->state;
9562 goto yyloop;
9563#endif /* YYBTYACC */
9564
9565yyoverflow:
9566 YYERROR_CALL("yacc stack overflow");
9567#if YYBTYACC
9568 goto yyabort_nomem;
9569yyenomem:
9570 YYERROR_CALL("memory exhausted");
9571yyabort_nomem:
9572#endif /* YYBTYACC */
9573 yyresult = 2;
9574 goto yyreturn;
9575
9576yyabort:
9577 yyresult = 1;
9578 goto yyreturn;
9579
9580yyaccept:
9581#if YYBTYACC
9582 if (yyps->save) goto yyvalid;
9583#endif /* YYBTYACC */
9584 yyresult = 0;
9585
9586yyreturn:
9587#if defined(YYDESTRUCT_CALL)
9588 if (yychar != YYEOF && yychar != YYEMPTY)
9589#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
9590 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding token", yychar, &yylval, &yylloc);
9591#else
9592 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding token", yychar, &yylval);
9593#endif /* defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED) */
9594
9595 {
9596 YYSTYPE *pv;
9597#if defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED)
9598 YYLTYPE *pp;
9599
9600 for (pv = yystack.l_base, pp = yystack.p_base; pv <= yystack.l_mark; ++pv, ++pp)
9601 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding state",
9602 yystos[*(yystack.s_base + (pv - yystack.l_base))], pv, pp);
9603#else
9604 for (pv = yystack.l_base; pv <= yystack.l_mark; ++pv)
9605 YYDESTRUCT_CALL("cleanup: discarding state",
9606 yystos[*(yystack.s_base + (pv - yystack.l_base))], pv);
9607#endif /* defined(YYLTYPE) || defined(YYLTYPE_IS_DECLARED) */
9608 }
9609#endif /* defined(YYDESTRUCT_CALL) */
9610
9611#if YYBTYACC
9612 if (yyerrctx)
9613 {
9614 yyFreeState(yyerrctx);
9615 yyerrctx = NULL;
9616 }
9617 while (yyps)
9618 {
9619 YYParseState *save = yyps;
9620 yyps = save->save;
9621 save->save = NULL;
9622 yyFreeState(save);
9623 }
9624 while (yypath)
9625 {
9626 YYParseState *save = yypath;
9627 yypath = save->save;
9628 save->save = NULL;
9629 yyFreeState(save);
9630 }
9631#endif /* YYBTYACC */
9632 yyfreestack(&yystack);
9633 return (yyresult);
9634}
